## Phase 5.5: Authentication Hardening

### Security Changes

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| Plaintext password comparison | `bcryptjs` hash verification |
| Hardcoded JWT secret in code | `JWT_SECRET` from `.env` |
| Hardcoded admin email/password | `ADMIN_EMAIL` + `ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH` from `.env` |
| HTML redirect on auth failure | JSON-only error responses |

**Key Files:**

- [auth.js utility](file:///D:/projects/SSC%20website/backend/utils/auth.js) вЂ” `verifyPassword()`, `generateToken()`, `verifyToken()`
- [authController.js](file:///D:/projects/SSC%20website/backend/controllers/authController.js) вЂ” env-driven login
- [authMiddleware.js](file:///D:/projects/SSC%20website/backend/middlewares/authMiddleware.js) вЂ” JSON-only error responses
- [.env.example](file:///D:/projects/SSC%20website/backend/.env.example) вЂ” template for developers

**Required `.env` variables:**
```
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@ssc.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=$2a$10$...  # bcrypt hash
JWT_SECRET=your_secure_random_string
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=1d
```

